Key Match Events: Gibraltar held Wales to a 0-0 draw, ending their 13-match losing streak.
Wales managed 17 shots but were unable to score.
Gibraltar had only 21% possession and managed just a single shot.
Pre-Game Insights: BBC Sport Wales noted that Gibraltar was in the midst of their worst losing streak in history with 13 consecutive defeats and an aggregate score of 0-50.
Post-Match Reflections: Wales fans booed Rob Page and called for his sacking after the match.
Rob Page acknowledged the fans' frustrations and emphasized the importance of focusing on the bigger picture.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Gibraltar's Football Association trolled Wales on social media with a GIF from the US Office in response to a BBC Wales post about their losing streak.
